{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 28,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 28 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:1",
      "text": "The ungodly man flees when no one pursues: but the righteous is confident as a lion.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:2",
      "text": "By reason of the sins of ungodly men quarrels arise; but a wise man will quell them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:3",
      "text": "A bold man oppresses the poor by ungodly deeds. As an impetuous and unprofitable rain,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:4",
      "text": "so they that forsake the law praise ungodliness; but they that love the law fortify themselves with a wall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:5",
      "text": "Evil men will not understand judgement: but they that seek the Lord will understand everything.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:6",
      "text": "A poor man walking in truth is better than a rich liar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:7",
      "text": "A wise son keeps the law: but he that keeps up debauchery dishonours his father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:8",
      "text": "He that increases his wealth by usuries and unjust gains, gathers it for him that pities the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:9",
      "text": "He that turns away his ear from hearing the law, even he has made his prayer abominable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:10",
      "text": "He that causes upright men to err in an evil way, himself shall fall into destruction: transgressor also shall pass by prosperity, but shall not enter into it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:11",
      "text": "A rich man is wise in his own conceit; but an intelligent poor man will condemn him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:12",
      "text": "By reason of the help of righteous men great glory arises: but in the places of the ungodly men are caught.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:13",
      "text": "He that covers his own ungodliness shall not prosper: but he that blames himself shall be loved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:14",
      "text": "Blessed is the man who religiously fears always: but the hard of heart shall fall into mischiefs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:15",
      "text": "A hungry lion and a thirsty wolf is he, who, being poor, rules over a poor nation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:16",
      "text": "A king in need of revenues is a great oppressor: but he that hates injustice shall live a long time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:17",
      "text": "He that becomes surety for a man charged with murder shall be an exile, and not in safety. Chasten thy son, and he shall love thee, and give honour to thy soul: he shall not obey a sinful nation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:18",
      "text": "He that walks justly is assisted: but he that walks in crooked ways shall be entangled therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:19",
      "text": "He that tills his own land shall be satisfied with bread: but he that follows idleness shall have plenty of poverty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:20",
      "text": "A man worthy of credit shall be much blessed: but the wicked shall not be unpunished.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:21",
      "text": "He that reverences not the persons of the just is not good: such a one will sell a man for a morsel of bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:22",
      "text": "An envious man makes haste to be rich, and knows not that the merciful man will have the mastery over him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:23",
      "text": "He that reproves a man’s ways shall have more favour than he that flatters with the tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:24",
      "text": "He that casts off father or mother, and thinks he sins not; the same is partaker with an ungodly man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:25",
      "text": "An unbelieving man judges rashly: but he that trusts in the Lord will act carefully.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:26",
      "text": "He that trusts to a bold heart, such an one is a fool: but he that walks in wisdom shall be safe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:27",
      "text": "He that gives to the poor shall not be in want: but he that turns away his eye from him shall be in great distress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.28.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 28:28",
      "text": "In the places of ungodly men the righteous mourn: but in their destruction the righteous shall be multiplied.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
